      "rationale": "Nonlinear Newton-Raphson solver residuals monitored across all 120 load increments. Maximum force residual norm 3.2e-5; maximum displacement residual norm 2.7e-5; energy residual 4.1e-7. All within prescribed tolerances. No divergence or spurious oscillation detected."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing reviewed by a second qualified analyst independent of the model developer; discrepancies resolved and documented.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of model setup, load application, boundary conditions, contact definitions, and QoI extraction scripts conducted by a senior FEA engineer not involved in original model development. Three minor discrepancies identified and corrected prior to final simulation runs. Review documented in project record PR-2026-0034."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear-elastic with bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity for Ti-6Al-4V; frictional Lagrange contact at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces. Model form justified by literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) constitutive model for Ti-6Al-4V validated against published tensile coupon data (Donachie 2000). UHMWPE block modelled as linear elastic; sensitivity analysis confirms <1% QoI sensitivity to block modulus variation of ±20%. Frictional contact (μ=0.3) at metal interfaces consistent with published tribology data. Model form assessed as appropriate for the compression-bending COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon testing; geometry from nominal CAD with tolerance sensitivity analysis; boundary conditions matched to F1717 test fixture drawings.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and tangent modulus for Ti-6Al-4V taken from DS-MAT-001 (lot-characterization batch, dataVintage 2025-10-15). Although DS-MAT-001 predates the January 2026 model revision, the material property values were not expected to change and re-validation is planned for the next submission cycle. Geometry inputs from DS-GEOM-002 (Rev C, 2026-01-18). Boundary conditions replicate F1717 fixture per test laboratory drawings. Sensitivity analysis shows QoIs vary <3% across tolerance envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 production-representative constructs from at least two independent lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to nominal geometry within drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from two production lots. Dimensional inspection of all screws and rods confirmed conformance to drawing tolerances. Constructs assembled by trained laboratory technicians per ASTM F1717 protocol. Sample representativeness assessed as adequate for Medium credibility requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two load levels or environmental conditions relevant to the COU; inter-laboratory reproducibility demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard compression-bending geometry) across two laboratories. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness QoI is 3.1%, confirming reproducibility. However, only one test condition (standard F1717 geometry) was evaluated; no variation in screw angulation or rod diameter was included. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3. This gap is acknowledged and does not prevent overall acceptance given all other factors meeting or exceeding required levels."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to test specimen parameters within documented tolerances; traceability matrix provided.",
      "rationale": "Traceability matrix maps each FEA input parameter to the corresponding test measurement or specification: screw OD (FEA 7.50 mm; measured mean 7.499 mm ± 0.003 mm), rod diameter (FEA 5.50 mm; measured 5.498 mm ± 0.002 mm), UHMWPE block modulus (FEA 0.94 GPa; DS-MAT-001 measured 0.93 ± 0.02 GPa), friction coefficient assumed 0.30 per literature. All parameters within acceptable equivalency bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "E/uval < 1.96 and relative QoI difference < 10% for all three primary QoIs; statistical comparison accounts for experimental variability via combined uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria. Stiffness: 4.2% difference, E/uval=0.87. Yield force: 6.8% difference, E/uval=1.41. Force at 40 mm: 7.9% difference, E/uval=1.63. Combined validation uncertainty computed per ASME V&V 40 Appendix B methodology incorporating simulation numerical uncertainty and experimental measurement uncertainty. No QoI exceeds acceptance bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the COU decision; clinical relevance of each QoI documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the anterior column and correlates with clinical stability. Yield force is the primary safety-relevant QoI linked to implant fatigue and fracture risk. Force at 40 mm displacement characterises post-yield energy absorption relevant to catastrophic failure assessment. All three QoIs are standard ASTM F1717 metrics and directly support the regulatory decision on construct mechanical adequacy."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
